                <head>No. 736.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Noyes</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Noyes</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Paris:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>[Inform minister of foreign affairs that Venezuela wants the United States to
                    receive and disburse, as trustee, the increased monthly payments of the
                    diplomatic debt, in a ratio to be adjusted.</p>
                <pb facs="1336" n="1212" xml:id="pg_1212"/>
                <p>While the United States may consent to receive and pay the monthly payments for
                    herself and other nations, it would not consent to guarantee any of the debt of
                    Venezuela.</p>
                <p>The United States requests France to delay action respecting her debt while the
                    former has this proposition under consideration.</p>
                <p>State that the United States offers its kind offices for adjustment of any
                    disagreement between Venezuela and France.</p>
                <p>Prompt action in this behalf requested.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
